From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 08:40:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] kati: add per-instance Evaluator.working_dir (logical-cwd
 foundation)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

kati's path-resolving boundaries (makefile read, `include`,
$(wildcard)/$(abspath)/$(realpath)/$(file), the find emulator root) currently
resolve relative paths against the *process* cwd — today made to work by
katirun doing std::env::set_current_dir for -C. That blocks running embedded
make as an in-process brush builtin: the builtin must resolve against the
brush shell's logical cwd WITHOUT chdir'ing the process, and concurrent
in-process instances in different directories must not race on it.

Introduce a per-instance `working_dir` on the Evaluator, seeded from the
process cwd so standalone rkati and the corpus are byte-identical
(KATI_COMPAT_PASS=364/378, fail=0). The boundaries will be threaded to resolve
against this in follow-up commits — carefully, since makefile/include paths
appear in output ($(MAKEFILE_LIST), $(abspath), parse-error Loc strings), so
resolution must redirect the fs access while preserving the original name for
display. The cwd-sensitive caches (file_cache, glob, find) then stay global
but key by the absolute path resolved at the boundary — correct and shareable
across instances, minimal churn.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01XyA6FzC6QGgsrjEYEBJV46
---
 src-rs/eval.rs | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src-rs/eval.rs b/src-rs/eval.rs
index f150c5a..a5d5fef 100644
--- a/src-rs/eval.rs
+++ b/src-rs/eval.rs
@@ -251,6 +251,14 @@ pub struct Evaluator {
     /// per-instance. Behind Arc<Mutex> so a ScopedGlobalVar can restore its
     /// saved binding on Drop without needing an &Evaluator.
     pub global_vars: Arc<Mutex<Vec<Option<Var>>>>,
+    /// sarun: per-instance logical working directory. kati's path-resolving
+    /// boundaries (makefile read, `include`, `$(wildcard)`/`$(abspath)`/
+    /// `$(realpath)`/`$(file)`, the find emulator root) resolve relative paths
+    /// against THIS instead of the process cwd, so an in-process `make` builtin
+    /// can run against the brush shell's logical cwd without `chdir`-ing the
+    /// process — and concurrent instances in different directories don't race
+    /// on it. Seeded from the process cwd so standalone rkati is unchanged.
+    pub working_dir: std::path::PathBuf,
     pub rules: Vec<Rule>,
     pub exports: HashMap<Symbol, bool>,
     /// sarun: set when the makefile names `.EXPORT_ALL_VARIABLES` as a
@@ -316,6 +324,7 @@ impl Evaluator {
         let ev = Self {
             rule_vars: HashMap::new(),
             global_vars: Arc::new(Mutex::new(Vec::new())),
+            working_dir: std::env::current_dir().unwrap_or_default(),
             rules: Vec::new(),
             exports: HashMap::new(),
             export_all_vars: false,
